No, ionustron, we're not against expansion chips ! What you made is in fact very cool. It's true the N106 is REALLY overkill, but it's nice to use it anyway !<br />The only thing I'd be against is people that use more than an expansion chip at a time. I happened to find a .nsf of Chrono Cross' intro which sounded good but it was using FDS + N106 + VRC7 which noes not make any sense. <br /><br />It would never be possible to convert it on .nes format, let alone to a cartridge. Also, it's not possible to test N106 stuff on the real hardware with a real N106 because all known carts are made of non-replacable epoxy blobs, but what you did with the N106 is cool nevertheless.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Aug 20, 2010 2:37 am</p><hr />
